{"heading":"The children of Israel sing the song of Moses—They extol the Lord as a man of war and rejoice in their deliverance from Egypt—The waters of Marah are healed—The Lord promises to free Israel from the diseases of Egypt.","number":15,"verseCount":27,"verses":[[1,["Then ",["sang",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Singing","tg/singing"],"."]]]," Moses and the children of Israel this song unto the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],", and spake, saying, I will ",["sing",["study-note-ref","b",[["Hosea 2:15","ot/hosea/2.15"],"."]]]," unto the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],", for he hath triumphed gloriously: the horse and his rider hath he thrown into the sea."]],[2,["The ",[[["Lord",["study-note-ref","a",[["2 Ne. 22:2","bofm/2-ne/22.2"],"."]]],["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," my ",["strength",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Priesthood, Power of","tg/priesthood-power-of"],"; ",["Strength","tg/strength"],"."]]]," and song, and he is become my ",["salvation",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Jesus Christ, Savior","tg/jesus-christ-savior"],"."]]],": he ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," my God, and I will ",["prepare him an habitation",["study-note-ref","d",["HEB praise Him."]]],"; my father’s God, and I will ",["exalt",["study-note-ref","e",[["2 Sam. 22:47","ot/2-sam/22.47"],"."]]]," him."]],[3,["The ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," a man of ",["war",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG War","tg/war"],"."]]],": the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," his ",["name",["study-note-ref","b",[["Jer. 16:21","ot/jer/16.21"],"."]]],"."]],[4,["Pharaoh’s ",["chariots",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 14:7 (5–7)","ot/ex/14.7"],"."]]]," and his host hath he ",["cast",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ex. 14:28 (27–30)","ot/ex/14.28"],"."]]]," into the sea: his chosen captains also are drowned in the ",["Red sea",["study-note-ref","c",["OR Reed Sea (also ",["v. 22","ot/ex/15.22"],")."]]],"."]],[5,["The depths have covered them: they sank into the bottom as a ",["stone",["study-note-ref","a",[["Neh. 9:11","ot/neh/9.11"],"."]]],"."]],[6,["Thy ",["right",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ps. 98:1","ot/ps/98.1"],"."]]]," ",["hand",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ps. 118:16 (15–16)","ot/ps/118.16"],"."]]],", O ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],", is become glorious in power: thy right hand, O ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],", hath dashed in pieces the enemy."]],[7,["And in the greatness of thine excellency thou hast overthrown them that rose up against thee: thou sentest forth thy wrath, ",["which",["clarity-word"]]," consumed them as ",["stubble",["study-note-ref","a",[["Isa. 47:14","ot/isa/47.14"],"; ",["1 Ne. 22:23 (15, 23)","bofm/1-ne/22.23"],"; ",["D&C 29:9","dc-testament/dc/29.9"],"; ",["JS—H 1:37","pgp/js-h/1.37"],"."]]],"."]],[8,["And with the blast of thy nostrils the ",["waters",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 14:21 (21–22)","ot/ex/14.21"],"."]]]," were gathered together, the floods stood upright as an ",["heap",["study-note-ref","b",[["Josh. 3:13","ot/josh/3.13"],"."]]],", ",["and",["clarity-word"]]," the depths were congealed in the heart of the sea."]],[9,["The enemy said, I will ",["pursue",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 14:9","ot/ex/14.9"],"."]]],", I will overtake, I will divide the spoil; my ",["lust",["study-note-ref","b",["HEB soul; i.e., desire. ",["TG Lust","tg/lust"],"."]]]," shall be satisfied upon them; I will draw my sword, my hand shall destroy them."]],[10,["Thou didst blow with thy wind, the sea covered them: they sank as lead in the mighty waters."]],[11,["Who ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," ",["like",["study-note-ref","a",[["2 Sam. 7:22","ot/2-sam/7.22"],"; ",["D&C 76:2 (1–4)","dc-testament/dc/76.2"],"."]]]," unto thee, O ",[[["Lord",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ps. 86:8","ot/ps/86.8"],"."]]],["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],", among the gods? who ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," like thee, glorious in ",["holiness",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Holiness","tg/holiness"],"."]]],", ",["fearful in praises",["study-note-ref","d",["OR to be praised with awe."]]],", doing wonders?"]],[12,["Thou stretchedst out thy right hand, the earth swallowed them."]],[13,["Thou in thy mercy hast ",["led",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ps. 77:20","ot/ps/77.20"],"; ",["1 Ne. 5:15","bofm/1-ne/5.15"],"; ",["17:31 (23–31)","bofm/1-ne/17.31"],"; ",["D&C 103:16 (16–18)","dc-testament/dc/103.16"],"."]]]," forth the people ",["which",["clarity-word"]]," thou hast redeemed: thou hast guided ",["them",["clarity-word"]]," in thy strength unto thy holy habitation."]],[14,["The people shall ",["hear",["study-note-ref","a",[["Josh. 2:11","ot/josh/2.11"],"; ",["5:1","ot/josh/5.1"],"."]]],", ",["and",["clarity-word"]]," be afraid: sorrow shall take hold on the inhabitants of ",["Palestina",["study-note-ref","b",["OR Philistia."]]],"."]],[15,["Then the ",["dukes",["study-note-ref","a",["HEB chiefs."]]]," of ",["Edom",["study-note-ref","b",[["Gen. 36:15 (15–43)","ot/gen/36.15"],"."]]]," shall be amazed; the mighty men of Moab, trembling shall take hold upon them; all the inhabitants of Canaan shall ",["melt",["study-note-ref","c",[["Josh. 2:9 (8–11)","ot/josh/2.9"],"."]]]," away."]],[16,[["Fear",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 23:27 (27–30)","ot/ex/23.27"],"; ",["Deut. 2:25","ot/deut/2.25"],"."]]]," and ",["dread",["study-note-ref","b",[["Josh. 2:9","ot/josh/2.9"],"."]]]," shall fall upon them; by the greatness of thine arm they shall be ",["as",["clarity-word"]]," still as a stone; till thy people pass over, O ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],", till the people pass over, ",["which",["clarity-word"]]," thou hast ",["purchased",["study-note-ref","c",[["Ps. 74:2","ot/ps/74.2"],"; ",["1 Cor. 6:20","nt/1-cor/6.20"],"."]]],"."]],[17,["Thou shalt bring them in, and plant them in the mountain of thine inheritance, ",["in",["clarity-word"]]," the place, O ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],", ",["which",["clarity-word"]]," thou hast made for thee to dwell in, ",["in",["clarity-word"]]," the ",["Sanctuary",["study-note-ref","a",[["1 Kgs. 8:13","ot/1-kgs/8.13"],"."]]],", O Lord, ",["which",["clarity-word"]]," thy hands have established."]],[18,["The ",[[["Lord",["study-note-ref","a",[["D&C 84:119","dc-testament/dc/84.119"],"."]]],["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," shall reign for ever and ever."]],[19,["For the horse of Pharaoh went in with his chariots and with his horsemen into the sea, and the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," brought again the waters of the sea upon them; but the children of Israel went on dry ",["land",["clarity-word"]]," in the midst of the sea."]],[20,[["¶ ",["para-mark"]],"And ",["Miriam",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 2:4","ot/ex/2.4"],"."]]]," the ",["prophetess",["study-note-ref","b",[["Judg. 4:4","ot/judg/4.4"],"; ",["Alma 32:23","bofm/alma/32.23"],"."]]],", the ",["sister",["study-note-ref","c",[["Ex. 2:4","ot/ex/2.4"],"; ",["Num. 26:59","ot/num/26.59"],"."]]]," of Aaron, took a ",["timbrel",["study-note-ref","d",[["1 Sam. 18:6 (6–7)","ot/1-sam/18.6"],"."]]]," in her hand; and all the women went out after her with timbrels and with dances."]],[21,["And Miriam answered them, ",["Sing",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Singing","tg/singing"],"."]]]," ye to the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],", for he hath triumphed gloriously; the horse and his rider hath he thrown into the sea."]],[22,["So Moses brought Israel from the Red sea, and they went out into the wilderness of ",["Shur",["study-note-ref","a",[["Gen. 16:7","ot/gen/16.7"],"."]]],"; and they went three days in the wilderness, and found no water."]],[23,[["¶ ",["para-mark"]],"And when they came to ",["Marah",["study-note-ref","a",["IE Bitterness."]]],", they could not drink of the waters of Marah, for they ",["were",["clarity-word"]]," bitter: therefore the name of it was called Marah."]],[24,["And the people ",["murmured",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Murmuring","tg/murmuring"],"."]]]," against Moses, saying, What shall we drink?"]],[25,["And he cried unto the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],"; and the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," shewed him a tree, ",["which",["clarity-word"]]," when he had cast into the waters, the ",["waters",["study-note-ref","a",[["2 Kgs. 2:21","ot/2-kgs/2.21"],"."]]]," were made sweet: there he made for them a statute and an ordinance, and there he ",["proved",["study-note-ref","b",[["Deut. 8:2","ot/deut/8.2"],"; ",["D&C 98:14 (12–14)","dc-testament/dc/98.14"],"; ",["124:55","dc-testament/dc/124.55"],"; ",["132:51","dc-testament/dc/132.51"],"; ",["Abr. 3:25","pgp/abr/3.25"],"."]]]," them,"]],[26,["And said, If thou wilt ",["diligently",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Diligence","tg/diligence"],"; ",["Perseverance","tg/perseverance"],"."]]]," ",["hearken",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Obedience","tg/obedience"],"."]]]," to the voice of the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," thy God, and wilt do that which is right in his sight, and wilt give ear to his commandments, and ",["keep",["study-note-ref","c",[["D&C 5:35","dc-testament/dc/5.35"],"; ",["11:20","dc-testament/dc/11.20"],"."]]]," all his statutes, I will put none of these ",["diseases",["study-note-ref","d",[["Deut. 7:15","ot/deut/7.15"],"."]]]," upon thee, which I have brought upon the Egyptians: for I ",["am",["clarity-word"]]," the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," that ",["healeth",["study-note-ref","e",[["TG Heal","tg/heal"],"."]]]," thee."]],[27,[["¶ ",["para-mark"]],"And they came to Elim, where ",["were",["clarity-word"]]," twelve wells of water, and ",["threescore and ten",["study-note-ref","a",["IE seventy palm trees."]]]," palm trees: and they encamped there by the waters."]]],"volume":"ot"}